I go into the kuhnya and put the teapot on the stove. Light matches, a couple of seconds looking at it, turn the handle of the gas stove, and I present a match to the burner. Flaring flames. The flame is blue. Smooth. I look at the fire and kettle. Five minutes later, all over the kitchen rises wild stench. No wonder. After all, in a teapot - urine. Why urine in a teapot? Because I peed there ...